  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "You can register or update your mobile number with your UAN (Universal Account Number) through the following online and offline methods:\n\n**Online Methods (Recommended):**\n\n*   **EPFO Member e-SEWA Portal:** This is the most common and straightforward method.\n\n    1.  **Visit the EPFO Member e-SEWA Portal:** Go to [https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/)\n    2.  **Sign In:** Log in using your UAN, password, and captcha.\n    3.  **Manage Section:** Navigate to the \"Manage\" section.\n    4.  **Select \"Contact Details\":** Click on \"Contact Details (to change Mobile No. & Email ID)\"\n    5.  **Enter New Mobile Number:** In the provided field, enter the new mobile number you want to register.\n    6.  **Get Authorization Pin:** Click on \"Get Authorization Pin\".  An OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to your Aadhaar-linked mobile number.\n    7.  **Enter OTP and Submit:** Enter the OTP received and click on \"Submit\".  Your mobile number will be updated after verification.\n\n*   **UMANG App (Unified Mobile Application for New-age Governance):**\n\n    1.  **Download and Install:** Download the UMANG app from your device's app store (Google Play Store for Android or App Store for iOS).\n    2.  **Register/Login:** If you're a new user, register on the app. If you already have an account, log in.\n    3.  **Search for EPFO:** Search for \"EPFO\" in the app.\n    4.  **Employee Centric Services:** Select \"Employee Centric Services\".\n    5.  **Raise Claim or Update KYC details**\n    6.  **Update Mobile Number:** Look for an option to update your mobile number. The exact wording may vary slightly depending on the app version.\n    7.  **Enter New Mobile Number:** Enter your new mobile number and follow the on-screen instructions for verification (usually involving an OTP sent to your Aadhaar-linked mobile number).\n\n**Important Considerations for Online Methods:**\n\n*   **Aadhaar Linking:** For a smooth online update, ensure your UAN is linked with your Aadhaar number. The OTP is usually sent to the mobile number registered with Aadhaar.\n*   **Mobile Number Verification:** The updated mobile number needs to be verified using an OTP. Make sure you have access to the mobile number you're trying to register.\n*   **Active UAN:** Your UAN must be activated before you can use these online services.  If it's not activated, you'll need to activate it on the EPFO portal.\n\n**Offline Method (Less Common and May Not Be Available):**\n\n*   **Contact Your Employer:**  In some cases, you might need to contact your employer's HR or PF department. They may have a process for updating mobile numbers through their company's EPFO interface. This method is becoming less common as EPFO promotes online updates.  Ask them if they can help update the details or direct you towards the correct procedure.\n\n**Troubleshooting Tips:**\n\n*   **UAN Activation:** If you haven't activated your UAN, do so before attempting to update your mobile number.  You'll need your UAN, date of birth, and either your member ID or Aadhaar/PAN details to activate it.\n*   **Aadhaar-Linked Mobile Number:** If you are not receiving the OTP to your entered mobile number, then check whether your Aadhaar is linked to your mobile number. If it is not linked, then you will have to get it linked through UIDAI.\n*   **Incorrect Details:** Double-check the details you're entering (UAN, date of birth, etc.) to ensure they are correct.\n*   **Portal Issues:** Sometimes, the EPFO portal might have technical issues.  Try again later if you encounter errors.\n*   **Employer Assistance:** If you're facing persistent problems, reach out to your employer's HR or PF department for assistance.\n*   **EPFO Helpdesk:** If all else fails, contact the EPFO customer care or helpdesk for assistance.  You can find their contact information on the EPFO website.\n\n**In summary, the easiest and most efficient way to register your mobile number with your UAN is through the EPFO Member e-SEWA portal or the UMANG app, provided your UAN is activated and linked with your Aadhaar and you have access to your Aadhaar-linked mobile number for OTP verification.**\n",
